<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="223" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1448,1727]" box="[151,967,1484,1512]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1484,1511]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Distribution:</emphasis>
Central Asia to Europe, west to 
<collectingCountry box="[671,769,1485,1511]" name="Slovenia" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M. A." box="[783,955,1485,1512]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" pagination="1 - 139" refId="ref21456" refString="Lieftinck, M. A. (1968) A review of old world species of Thyreus Panzer (= Crocisa Jurine) (Hym., Apoidea, Anthophoridae) Part 4. Palaearctic species. Zoologische Verhandelingen, 98, 1 - 139." type="journal article" year="1968">Lieftinck 1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1448,1727]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,227,1521,1547]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Notes:</emphasis>
Reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[403,498,1521,1547]" name="Portugal" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Portugal</collectingCountry>
by Dusmet (1931) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Diniz, M. A." box="[760,905,1520,1547]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref20854" refString="Diniz, M. A. (1959) Estado actual do conhecimento dos himenopteros de Portugal. Memorias e Estudos do Museu Zoologico da Universidade de Coimbra, 259, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1959">Diniz (1959)</bibRefCitation>
, these are probably misidentifications given the disjunct distribution—these are the only records reported from Western Europe. Lieftinck studied material from the museum of the University of 
<collectingRegion box="[564,662,1593,1619]" country="Portugal" name="Coimbra" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Coimbra</collectingRegion>
where Diniz’s material was stored, so it is highly likely that he would have come across it during his revision but there is no mention of it (misidentified or otherwise) in his 1968 revision, so we take a conservative approach and remove it from the current Portuguese list until this material can be directly inspected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
